<h2 class="">Message From The Principal<br>
</h2>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">Dear Parents/Guardians:</p>
<p class="">I want to thank all of you for your support and effort during these difficult times. The spread of Covid-19 has changed education and created challenges. We would like to express how proud we are of our students and the work that they are accomplishing during this time. We encourage our students and families to do the best that you can. We understand the difficulties under these circumstances and are understanding and empathetic to the difficulties our students face at this time. We appreciate our students as well as their families and their continued efforts through this time.</p>
<p class="">We would like to express our understanding and our sincere sadness for the uncertainty of high school graduation as well as 8th-grade promotion. We are very proud of you and the accomplishments that you all have achieved. While we are uncertain what our options are at this time, we are looking into ideas to celebrate graduation and promotion. We commit to doing the best we can to offer a celebration for our graduates at this time if it is safe and permitted.</p>
<p class="">Thank you for all you do for our school and your students.</p>
<p class="">Thanks,<br>Andrew Brogan</p>
